                    estimate the long‑term average annual rate of soil erosion
                    by rainfall and runoff. It multiplies five factors—R, K, LS,
                    C and P—to predict soil loss per unit area. It has been the
                    basis for many conservation planning tools and later
                    revisions such as RUSLE and RUSLE2.
